Went here with my boyfriend on Veteran’s day because we got an email from Smoothie King saying to stop by for free Veteran’s day smoothies. Him and I being both Vets, we decided to stop by our fav go to place after our run at 10am.  We are told by the cashier that he can’t offer us the special bc he hasn’t received guidance from Corporate. It’s 10am, the store’s been open for a couple of hours and he’s already had 4 people ahead of us asking for the same thing.  How does corporate not tell their employees in one of the biggest Military ran districts about the offer weeks ahead? Let alone the morning before the store opens???  Not worth going to this hole in the wall location, besides, they don’t even have doorknobs on their doors. So you’re lucky to even get in if the door’s cracked. Maybe that should have been a red flag.  Never coming here again.

I work right across the street, I was so excited. I love the peanut power plus shake it is crave worthy. However this Smoothie King always has a wait and lacks basic customer service. The two times I went I had extended waits but it was one woman working very hard, I understood. I also noted they didnt seem to be staffed correctly. This morning I attempt to order a Smoothie but left without one after not being able to order for 10 minutes. A customer came in behind me who must have mobiled ordered because the attendant printed a reciept and told them to wait in the Smoothie line. Meanwhile I have still not ordered and the attendant didnt even acknowledge me to say I will help you in a minute, good morning, not even to explain why she helped the man behind me prior. Three strikes no good experience, your done.  Make sure you have a full 30 minutes to get ur Smoothie or dont try.

I'm loyal to Smoothie King and love them. However this location has horrible customer service.  I think there is only 2 associates there who is very good but that is during the day. The evening associates have bad attitudes, lack effort, and efficiency (I just left there @ 6:10pm).  My card has a bad stripe for swiping. The guy tells me card declined. I checked my account and have funds there. He didn't bother to enter my card manually. I work in retail so I know how it can be done. They always get my order wrong as well. So do yourself a favor avoid the evening time and stick to the day.

Best Smoothie King in DC! I'm a frequent customer here and the employees are ALWAYS providing excellent customer service. The employees are also extremely friendly and welcoming - this goes for Sarita, Sara, de Jesus and Workineh! You guys are awesome.
